{
  "stem": "935.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my sister with her husband was sent, which we didn't know for many, many, many months where they were.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after a few days in this place, which was-- you had the feeling everybody is a zombie, asleep.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know whether they were afraid because they were so close to the German border or what it was or whether they hadn't gotten over the invasion yet.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I can't tell you, but it was very weird.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I had found the committee-- Jewish committee whatever-- little man there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I told him I couldn't stay here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I needed to be where I could work-- you know, no money, no nothing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he gave me permission to go to a place called Utrecht-- U-T-R-E-C-H.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's in the south of Holland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It's known for being very cultural, for a very, very good university and a beautiful theatre, which were both closed now.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, and my mother, unfortunately, had to stay in this awful place, Enschede.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I remember, much later, thinking, if I told him I was an actress, I needed to go somewhere else, if I would have thought of, I would have told him that mama was an actress, too.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So she could have gotten out with me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It took many months until I got her out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Then I was in Utrecht, which, as I said, I knew from my tours with the-- with the theatre in The Hague.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I knew every place in, in Holland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And what I did there was all the people who had been evacuated-- they were Jewish-Dutch families took them in.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the Jewish committee would give us pocket money, which was very nice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Jews-- you know, Dutch Jews would give to them and they would give to us.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
